Public - The class is accessible by any other class

Default - The class is only accessible by classes in the same packege. This is when you
don't specify a modifier.

Private - The code is only accessible with the declared class.

Protected - the code is accessible in the same package and subclasses.

Non-Access Modifiers

final - The class cannot be inherited by other Classes.
abstract - The Class cannot used to create objects (To access an abstract class, it must be
inherited for another class.

for Attributes and Methods

final - Attribute and methods cannot be overridden/Modified
static - Attribute and Methods belongs to the class, rather than an object.
abstract - Can only be used in an abstract class, and can only be used on methods. the
method does not have a body, for example abstract void run();. the body is provided by
the subclass (inherited from).
transient - Attribute and methods are skkiped when serializing object containing them
synchronized - methods can only be accessed by one thread at time.
volatize - the value of a attribute is not catched thread-locally, and is awalys read from
the "main memory"
